From 58042f2127cc0f35ea0bd9615f6c9548b10ae3f7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Narendhar Reddy <nare@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Wed, 7 May 2025 22:28:18 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] ath12k: boot time optimisation along with cleanup.

1)Parallel calbration request to FW
Currently, QMI initialization for a radio occurred only after the
calibration of the preceding radio was completed. Change this code flow
to allow QMI initialization for each radio independently, without waiting
for other radios to complete calibration.

2) Sending host cap parallely.
Currently, once calibration is completed, the host capability event is
triggered for one radio. The host capability event for the next radio is only
triggered after the firmware ready event is received for the first radio.
Improve this by triggering the host cap event for all radios simultaneously.

3) Calibaration in Mission mode supported by FW
Currently, cold boot mode is sent to firmware, and calibration is performed in
cold boot mode. After calibration completes, the radio is powered down/up, and
mission mode is sent to firmware. FW as part of new feature supports calibration in
mission mode, change this code flow to send mission mode to
firmware and wait for calibration to complete, avoid power down/up.
FW indicates support for calibration in mission mode through a bit in phy cap.
Modify host to send the calibration bit while sending mode to indicate fw for calibration.

Signed-off-by: Narendhar Reddy <nare@qti.qualcomm.com>
